{"TopicId":162854,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Logitech Extreme 3D Pro Joystick","CreatedByName":"The Raging Sandwich","CreatedById":164377,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-03T20:17:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"The Raging Sandwich","CreatedById":164377,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-03T20:17:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I just got it and I know exactly nothing about it. How exactly do I get it to work for KSP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-04T02:59:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShouldn\u0027t require anything beyond plugging it in and running a calibration through Windows control panel. You can assign functions to buttons through the normal KSP settings customization.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-04T07:22:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnice! I have it me too but I never tried to configure it for ksp.\u003Cbr\u003E\nhow do you wanna use it? \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E control when docking? pilot an airplane? other?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nanyway...this is what I really would like to have:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/160273-ksp-controller/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-04T07:49:56Z\u0022 title=\u002207/04/2017 07:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by antipro\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Raging Sandwich","CreatedById":164377,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-04T15:53:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223110474\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022162854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499152928\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnice! I have it me too but I never tried to configure it for ksp.\u003Cbr\u003E\nhow do you wanna use it? \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E control when docking? pilot an airplane? other?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nanyway...this is what I really would like to have:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/160273-ksp-controller/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust about anything manned. I want to go for realism so launches and anything unmanned is autopilot and manned flights like planes and spacecraft I want to use with the joystick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-04T16:17:04Z\u0022 title=\u002207/04/2017 04:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 4, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by The Raging Sandwich\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Raging Sandwich","CreatedById":164377,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-04T16:18:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do I assign functions to stick movements?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-04T17:12:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223110866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022162854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499185122\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164377\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Raging Sandwich\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, The Raging Sandwich said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do I assign functions to stick movements?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the KSP settings screen, there\u0027s a column for buttons and another column for controller axes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Raging Sandwich","CreatedById":164377,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-04T18:51:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223110952\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022162854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499188369\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the KSP settings screen, there\u0027s a column for buttons and another column for controller axes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI figured it out now, thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-31T18:40:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have one too!(its easy to set up)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"therapymiles","CreatedById":180295,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-01T02:16:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223111119\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022162854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499194261\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164377\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Raging Sandwich\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/4/2017 at 0:51 PM, The Raging Sandwich said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI figured it out now, thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow? i just got my extreme 3d pro and am having trouble. the game (1.3) recognizes the joystick in the input settings but not correctly. For example pitch axis is automatically assigned to joy0.3, when i try to reassign it to joy0.1 (forward or back on the stick) it recognizes the input and changes it to joy0.1, until I hit accept and then it reverts it back to joy0.3 automatically. long story short, it knows the controller is there but does not keep any of the settings. please and thanks for the help/info.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MiffedStarfish","CreatedById":175356,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-04T09:41:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm. I also have a Extreme 3D Pro, (let\u0027s start a club!) and I didn\u0027t have any of those issues. One issue i did have however, was that even after accepting the new inputs the game wouldn\u0027t recognise them without closing down and starting it up again. Try that, it might fix it. Good luck!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryan.Bayguzin","CreatedById":197263,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-04T02:25:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello folks I\u0027m new to KSP and I have a 3d pro too!\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a funny story you have going on and I might be able to help you case my dad is a engineer who can fix the glitches.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}